  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Minlaparotomy (MC) and laparoscopic cholecystoctomy (LC) are commonly applied surgical
      techniques for the management of symptomatic gallstone disease and both techiques have shown
      to be feasible for day surgery. However, to our knowledge the long-term outcome between
      these approaches has not been compared in randomised trials as day surgery procedures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
